title: Abott and Costello Red Crayola Division sketch
definition: A live, protocol-like routine that riffs on Abbott and Costello's comedic timing with Red Crayola's experimental energy to dramatize how division works in real time.
protoExample: Performers act out the bit onstage, treating each mathematical step as a call-and-response rule between straight man and clown.
examples: Breaking a 28รท7 exchange into beats so every 'protocol' handoff lands a punchline.
Using props and crayons to mark each division step as if following a standard operating procedure.
Letting the refrain 'Division sure is easy.' close the routine like a successful handshake signal.
when: Mid-20th century comedy energy, reenacted live
